QueryText: ONION SOWING
KCCAns: Onions can be grown from seeds and sets. In the first method, about 10-12kg seeds are sown to raise seedlings for one hectare and area wise about 5% area is required to raise seedlings for one hectare. The seeds after treatment with thiram or captan (2-3g/kg seed) are sown in raised (15-20cm) nursery beds of 3mx0.6m size with a distance of 70cm between the beds.
